  "body": "**🧐 Motivation**\r\n\r\nSolidity version [`0.8.18`](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/releases/tag/v0.8.18) introduced the possibility to use named parameters in mapping types. Since the minimum pragma version was bumped to Solidity version `0.8.19` via https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/4288, I think it would make sense to implement this new feature to increase the overall code readability.\r\n\r\n**📝 Details**\r\n\r\nOZ contracts make extensive use of mappings, and this could be definitely a benefit:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nmapping(address owner => mapping(address spender => uint256 amount)) private _allowances;\r\n```",
